Pre-Game Insights: Austria has won just one of their previous five meetings with Serbia while Serbia has won the other three.
The two sides last faced off in a World Cup qualifying clash in 2017, which Austria won 3-2 with a late winner from Louis Schaub.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Tuesday's game will mark the fifth meeting between Austria and Serbia.
Austria thrashed Turkey 6-1 in their last match with four different players scoring including Michael Gregoritsch who netted a hat-trick.
Serbia picked up a narrow but deserved 1-0 win over Cyprus in their last outing with Sergej Milinkovic-Savic scoring the only goal seven minutes into the game.
